definitions.definition: A maritime traditional county of Wales , bounded to the north by the Irish Sea , to the northeast by the Dee estuary , to the east by Cheshire and to the south and southwest by Denbighshire . A detached part, Maelor Saesneg , is bounded on the northwest by Denbighshire , on the northeast by Cheshire , and on the south by Shropshire . There is a further small detached part around Marford.
A local government area of Wales . It borders Merseyside , Cheshire , Wrexham and Denbighshire .
